{
  "texts": [
    "More formally, let N = {1,..., n} be the set of available items and denote the no-purchase option by {0}.",
    "Then, N ∪ {0} refers to the selection of available items including the no-purchase option.",
    "The retailer needs to select a subset of the available items to be offered.",
    "Following Davis et al. (2013), instead of denoting the offer set as an actual subset, the assortment can be represented by a binary decision variable x i for each item i ∈ N that indicates whether this item is offered or not by set- ting x i = 1 and x i = 0, respectively.",
    "More formally, define Note that the no-purchase option is always offered, implying that x 0 = 1 holds for any assortment."
  ]
}